# ============================================================================
# _ldap_authz_proxy — zsh completion for **ldap_authz_proxy** —
#                      elonen/ldap_authz_proxy, the HTTP **LDAP
#                      authorization sidecar** for Nginx (and any
#                      other HTTP reverse proxy that speaks the
#                      `auth_request` protocol).  Pre-authenticated
#                      HTTP requests reach Nginx; Nginx forwards
#                      the username (extracted from any HTTP header
#                      — Kerberos `Authorization: Negotiate`,
#                      `X-Remote-User`, `Auth-User`, or a session
#                      cookie validated upstream) to `ldap_authz_proxy`
#                      via `auth_request` location; the proxy
#                      performs an LDAP query against Active
#                      Directory (or any RFC-4511 v3 LDAP server)
#                      to validate group membership, fetches typed
#                      attribute values, and returns them to Nginx
#                      as HTTP response headers that get injected
#                      into the upstream request to the protected
#                      service.  Rust=171 OPENING leg of new Axis
#                      116 (LDAP / RFC-4511 protocol) via the
#                      canonical Rust async LDAP client library
#                      **inejge/ldap3**.
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/elonen/ldap_authz_proxy
#   Maintainer : Jarno Elonen  (elonen@iki.fi)
