# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `elonen/ldap_authz_proxy` declares a **direct** dependency on
#   `ldap3` (the inejge/ldap3 canonical Rust LDAP client library)
#   in its `Cargo.toml`, and `src/main.rs` imports it directly via
#   `use ldap3::{LdapConnAsync, SearchEntry, ResultEntry};` and
#   uses the typed `ldap3::result::Result<LdapAnswer>` typed return
#   from its `ldap_query()` async helper.
#
#   `inejge/ldap3` is **THE canonical Rust LDAP client library** —
#   a pure-Rust LDAP v3 (RFC 4511) client built on the Tokio async
#   runtime, the de-facto LDAP-on-Rust dependency for every Rust
#   project that needs to talk to OpenLDAP / Microsoft Active
#   Directory / FreeIPA / Apple Open Directory / 389 Directory
#   Server / Oracle Internet Directory / Apache DS / Red Hat
#   Directory Server / Univention Corporate Server / Samba 4 AD
#   DC / Univention LDAP / lemmy-style "small LDAP server"
#   targets.  It exposes:
#
#     • Typed `LdapConnAsync::new(url)` /
#       `.with_settings(LdapConnSettings::new().set_starttls(
#       true).set_no_tls_verify(false).set_conn_timeout(d)
#       .set_keepalive(b))` async connection builder
#     • Typed `Ldap::simple_bind(dn, password)` /
#       `.sasl_external_bind()` / `.sasl_gssapi_bind(server_fqdn)`
#       / `.sasl_digest_md5_bind(realm, username, password)` /
#       `.sasl_external_bind()` typed bind methods
#     • Typed `Ldap::search(base, scope, filter, attrs)` /
#       `.streaming_search(...)` / `.streaming_search_with_settings
#       (...)` /  `.compare(dn, attr, value)` /  `.add(dn, attrs)` /
#       `.delete(dn)` /  `.modify(dn, mods)` /  `.modifydn(dn,
#       rdn, delete_old, new_sup)` /  `.extended(req)` /  `.abandon
#       (msgid)` typed operation methods
#     • Typed `Scope::Base` /  `Scope::OneLevel` /  `Scope::Subtree`
#       /  `Scope::Children` (the post-RFC-4511 extension scope)
#       enum
#     • Typed `Mod::Add(attr, vals)` /  `Mod::Delete(attr, vals)` /
#       `Mod::Replace(attr, vals)` /  `Mod::Increment(attr, vals)`
#       (RFC 4525) discriminated-union ModType
#     • Typed `SearchEntry::construct(entry)` with `entry.dn` /
#       `entry.attrs: HashMap<String, Vec<String>>` /
#       `entry.bin_attrs: HashMap<String, Vec<Vec<u8>>>` (for
#       binary attribute values like userCertificate;binary,
#       jpegPhoto, objectGUID, objectSid)
#     • Typed `LdapResult.rc` / `.matched` / `.text` / `.refs` /
#       `.ctrls` result envelope with the full set of LDAP result
