#       LDAP_NOT_ALLOWED_ON_RDN=67, LDAP_ALREADY_EXISTS=68,
#       LDAP_NO_OBJECT_CLASS_MODS=69, LDAP_RESULTS_TOO_LARGE=70,
#       LDAP_AFFECTS_MULTIPLE_DSAS=71, LDAP_OTHER=80,
#       LDAP_SERVER_DOWN=81, LDAP_LOCAL_ERROR=82, LDAP_ENCODING_ERROR
#       =83, LDAP_DECODING_ERROR=84, LDAP_TIMEOUT=85,
#       LDAP_AUTH_UNKNOWN=86, LDAP_FILTER_ERROR=87,
#       LDAP_USER_CANCELLED=88, LDAP_PARAM_ERROR=89, LDAP_NO_MEMORY
#       =90, LDAP_CONNECT_ERROR=91, LDAP_NOT_SUPPORTED=92,
#       LDAP_CONTROL_NOT_FOUND=93, LDAP_NO_RESULTS_RETURNED=94,
#       LDAP_MORE_RESULTS_TO_RETURN=95, LDAP_CLIENT_LOOP=96,
#       LDAP_REFERRAL_LIMIT_EXCEEDED=97 named numeric constants)
#     • Typed LDAP control support (RFC 4511 + RFC 3296 referrals,
#       RFC 2891 server-side sort, RFC 2696 paged-results,
#       RFC 5805 transactions, MSAD-specific
#       LDAP_SERVER_DIRSYNC_OID, LDAP_SERVER_NOTIFICATION_OID,
#       LDAP_SERVER_EXTENDED_DN_OID controls)
#     • Typed extended operations (RFC 4533 sync, RFC 3909 cancel,
#       RFC 2830 StartTLS, RFC 3062 password modify)
#     • Sync wrappers via `LdapConn` (the blocking-API alternative
#       to `LdapConnAsync` for non-tokio contexts)
#
#   `inejge/ldap3` powers every serious Rust LDAP integration in
#   production: kanidm/kanidm (the canonical Rust identity-and-
